name: Model
description: Type of the Machine used in the Switch

name: STP Change count
description: The MSTP count of topology changes in a specific instance.

name: Active version
description: The software version of the active image.

name: Backup Version

name: System IP
description: The switch's network ip address

name: Port 1 in octets

name: Port 1 in Err
description: For packet-oriented interfaces, the number of inbound packets that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. For character- oriented or fixed-length interfaces, the number of inbound transmission units that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

name: System UDP Incoming datagrams
description: The total number of UDP datagrams delivered to UDP users. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by discontinuities in the value of sysUpTime.

name: System UDP number ports
description: The total number of received UDP datagrams for which there was no application at the destination port. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by discontinuities in the value of sysUpTime.

name: System UDP Incoming errors
description: The number of received UDP datagrams that could not be delivered for reasons other than the lack of an application at the destination port. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by discontinuities in the value of sysUpTime.

name: System UDP outgoing datagrams
description: The total number of UDP datagrams sent from this entity. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by discontinuities in the value of sysUpTime.

name: Incoming SNMP packets
description: The total number of messages delivered to the SNMP entity from the transport service.

name: Outgoing SNMP packets
description: The total number of SNMP Messages which were passed from the SNMP protocol entity to the transport service.
